name: Cozy Cottage/Home Away from Home/Close2Attractions
transit: If you are flying into LAX and you arrive between 3 and 7PM on a weekday, we highly recommend stopping for dinner somewhere (Marina Del Rey or Culver City is nice) or simply just spend some time somewhere near LAX.  Then drive to our place around 7:30 PM.   It will make a huge difference in the amount of time you spend in traffic during rush hour. There is a bus stop at the end of our street, approximately a 3 minute walk.   Also, the Glendale Metrolink / Amtrack is about a 5 minute drive. Easy access to the 5, 2, 110, and 134 freeway, each less than 2 miles away, if not closer. 10 minutes to Downtown LA 10 minutes to Burbank 5   minutes to Glendale and Silverlake 15 minutes to Universal Studios 15 minutes to Hollywood Chinese Theater & Kodak Theater 15 minutes to Pasadena 20 minutes to The Grove & Farmers Market 25 minutes to West Hollywood 25 minutes to Santa Monica 30 minutes to West LA & UCLA 30 minutes to Beverly Hills 30 minutes to LAX 40 minutes to Disneyland 20 minutes to JPL

name: 5-Star Beverly Hills Suite
transit: Most use Lyft or Uber to get around. Between rental fees, gas and parking, can be cheaper than renting a car and they are allowed to pick you up at the upper departure area at LAX.  There are buses going in all directions surrounding me.  N/S buses going up and down La Cienega & Robertson.  And E/W buses going across Wilshire & Olympic.  None more than 2-4 blocks away.  The closest train is 10 minutes south in Culver City. There is also a new free smart phone app for coordinating your travel about the sprawling city that includes maps and routes for all buses and trains.  It's called Go511.

name: Frogtown 1BR w/ Skylight - LARiver Silver Lake adj
transit: We are not a walking neighborhood, although the best sandwiches in Los Angeles are a short walk down the river (Wax Paper Co). The LA River is a 5 minute walk from the house, the bus stop at Riverside & Newell is a 10-minute walk, and both Salazar and the Elysian pop-up restaurants are also a 10-minute walk through Frogtown. Other neighborhoods and anything else worth walking to is a 30-minute or way more trek. Bring or rent wheels! Multiple freeways are within a 3-minute drive.

name: Your home away from home /sleeps 4/ furnished
transit: Lois and Craig were great hosts and I really enjoyed my stay. Their Internet access is beyond fast - Verizon FIOS fiber to the home. If you are used to the typical awful cable company Internet, or even worse, the typically horribly slow hotel WiFi, staying here with truly fast Internet will be a real treat. If you are traveling without a car, their location is outstanding. They are walking distance to a number of excellent restaurants including a wonderful Indian restaurant called Bombay Tandoori. You are only two blocks away from Pacific Coast Highway where you have access to three bus lines. One line, Commuter Express, operates at the morning and evening rush hours and takes you quickly to and from downtown Los Angeles. From downtown LA you can go to San Francisco, Las Vegas, Phoenix, and other cities for $25 to $50 using Megabus, Tufesa, Hoang Express or other new carriers. If you are flying, you can take the MTA 232 bus from LAX and be dropped off two blocks from the house at Madis

transit: GETTING THERE:  From LAX take the FlyAway bus to Union Station, then take the Gold Line to the Little Tokyo stop. The building is two short blocks away.  Or take an Uber Pool or Lyft Line. GETTING AROUND:   Metro Bike Share Station- Nearest is at Traction and Rose, two blocks away.  Use it to explore DTLA! Dash A bus - Stop is at Hewitt and 2nd St, less than a block away.  Use it to explore DTLA!  Fare is 50 cents. Metro subway - Little Tokyo Gold Line stop is two blocks away at Alameda and 1st.  Use it to explore the rest of Los Angeles City and County! You can find us by doing a map search online for "7th and PCH 90814, USA" Many of our guests use this as a base to visit L.A., Disneyland (20 miles), Universal Studios (40 miles), Santa Monica (36 miles), Laguna Beach (31 miles) and all other Southern California attractions. We also highly recommend checking out the local shopping and beaches. We are a bike ride away from the Long Beach Aquarium and the Queen Mary. This is a fabulous place to visit.   Cal State Long Beach is walking distance and Long Beach Convention Center is 4.5 miles.  VISITING L.A.: If this is your first visit to Southern California and you intend to travel to see the sights, you should know that the Los Angeles area is spread out and it is very useful to have a car.
